version.name: EasyNegative
version.description:
This embedding should be used in your NEGATIVE prompt. Adjust the strength as desired (seems to scale well without any distortions), the strength required may vary based on positive and negative prompts.

Samples are, in order:

  1. sample01 - Counterfeit-V2.0.safetensors

  2. sample02 - AbyssOrangeMix2_sfw.safetensors

  3. sample03 - anything-v4.0-pruned.safetensors

  4. Strength comparison using AbyssOrangeMix2_sfw.


From Author
"This is a Negative Embedding trained with Counterfeit. Please use it in the "\stable-diffusion-webui\embeddings" folder. It can be used with other models, but the effectiveness is not certain."

version.name: v16.0
version.description:
Pony v16.0 is here - and this one is the result of listening, stepping back, and rebuilding with intent.

After extensive feedback from users, I deliberately took a step back from the previous direction, re-evaluated the foundations, and rebuilt from there. The result is a version that feels fresh, flexible, and experimental, while still staying true to the CyberRealistic identity.

If you’re looking for a rock-solid, predictable workhorse, I still recommend:

  • v14.x or v15.x - both remain excellent and stable choices

v16.0, however, is where the exciting stuff starts. It’s for users who enjoy testing, experimenting, and discovering new behaviors and capabilities.

version.name: Lightning DPM++ SDE
version.description:
Lightning version should be used at CFG scale 2 and with around 3-6 sampling steps. Should work with DPM++ SDE Karras (or Normal). It might work on other samplers, but please hold your judgement on anything that differs from the suggested settings.

Can be used for highres fix and tiled upscaling. Please check the examples.

If you train on this, make sure to use DPM++ SDE Karras at the correct target steps and cfg scale.

version.name: Final
version.description:
CyberRealistic SD1.5 ~Final Release~

This is it.
The last and final version of the original CyberRealistic SD1.5 model.
This release marks the end of an era and the moment where SD1.5 CyberRealistic reaches its ultimate form.

No more updates.
No more revisions.
Just the final, perfected vision of where it all began.

Thank you to everyone who supported, tested, created, and believed in CyberRealistic from day one.
The era of SD1.5 ends here.
The legacy continues.
